By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Sunday confirmed 838 new cases of #COVID-19 in Nigeria. In its report released on Sunday via it’s twitter handle account, the health agency stated that the total confirmed cases in Nigeria have risen to 84,414 out of which71,034 patients have been treated and discharged from across the various isolation facilities in Nigeria. This is also as the Centre reported that1,254 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications in Nigeria since the index case was reported. The health agency gave the list of states where the new cases were recorded as follows: FCT-297Lagos-253Plateau-82Kaduna-57Katsina-32Nasarawa-31Kano-25Gombe-24Oyo-8Rivers-8Zamfara-7Ogun-4Bauchi-4Edo-4Anambra-1Sokoto-1 According to the report, the breakdown of total confirmed cases in the 36 states of the federation including the FCT is stated below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 152 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. According to the report released via it's twitter handle late Tuesday, this brings total confirmed cases 64,336 out ot which 60,333 have been treated and discharged from various isolation… November 11, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Monday confirmed 157 new cases of #COVID-19 in Nigeria. The report released via it's twitter handle account said the fresh infections brought the total confirmed cases to 65,305 out of which 61,162 patients have been discharged… November 17, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID -19 in Nigeria recorded 255 infections as confirmed cases soared to 300 on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The health agency while disclosing this via it's twitter handle, said the other five states… November 9, 2020 In "Top Stories"